Why?

Usually, users don't want to be notified about their own modifications. 

 

It looks like we need 1 extra field, e.g. *lastUpdater* or *modificationUser* [here|https://support.atlassian.com/jira-service-management-cloud/docs/advanced-search-reference-jql-fields/#Advancedsearchingfieldsreference-LastViewedLastViewedDatelastViewedDateLastviewed].

JQL usage, e.g.:
{code:java}
lastUpdater != currentUser() {code}

The Slack integration in Jira does not display how many and which users currently have personal notifications configured with their Jira account. This could be important to figure the owner of the subscription.
h3. Workaround

You can get the related users using a SQL query along the lines of:
{code:java}
select cwd_user.lower_user_name, cwd_user.lower_display_name, cwd_user.lower_email_address from propertyentry, app_user, cwd_user  where property_key like '%slack%' and propertyentry.entity_id = app_user.id and app_user.id = cwd_user.id;
{code}
Keep in mind that the 
{code:java}
'%slack%'{code}
portion results in a really broad search and that you should narrow this to exactly the property that represents the connections / users you want.

h3. Issue Summary
When exporting issues using the Excel option, Jira does not respect the user's permissions. 
 !image-2021-04-09-14-14-39-645.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new group to be given to a user with Jira Software Product Access;
# Create a project and a couple of issues into it;
# Create a new permission scheme for the project and give the new group permission on this project;
# Make sure all other Permission Schemes are not using Any Logged in User application role;
# Impersonate the user with access to a single project;
# Access Advanced Search and use the Export to Excel option with the default JQL order by created DESC.

h3. Expected Results
The file should have the same result as the Jira JQL result. 
h3. Actual Results
All issues on the instance are exported meaning that permissions are not being checked.
h3. Workaround
 Currently there is no known workaround for this behavior. A workaround will be added here when available
